    https://firestore.googleapis.com/v1/projects/....

the service-worker intercepts the request and serves the latest response from cache, if available. So far so good.


I have a "force-refresh" button on the page. When clicked, I want the service-worker to ignore the request and let the browser do its job. It works fine, the parameter gets added to the request header :

    access-control-request-headers: ngsw-bypass

This parameter can be set as a request header or a request parameter in url.

Problem is, firebase complains about the extra parameter, set as request header or parameter, doesn't matter. 


    {
